author: Joe Dorish
title: Craziest Miami Dolphins NFL fans in 2015 (Photos)
text:
Craziest Miami Dolphins NFL fans in 2015 (Photos) Photo by Rob Foldy/Getty Images View all 17 photos The NFL has rabid fans of all kinds and one of the teams with the most rabid fan base is the Miami Dolphins. Some of those rabid Miami Dolphins fans like to show their support by dressing up in crazy but fitting outfits. Here is a slideshow of photos showing the craziest Miami Dolphins NFL fans from the 2015 season. Hope you like the photos and watch for the craziest Miami Dolphins fans at their games for the rest of the NFL season.
Photo by Rob Foldy/Getty Images The Dolphins are off to a 1-2 start in 2015. Miami beat the Washington Redskins in Week 1, but have lost to the Jacksonville Jaguars in Week 2 and the Buffalo Bills in Week 3. Miami will try to get back on track Sunday as they face the New York Jets in a game being played at Wembley Stadium in London, England. The start time for the game is 9:30 am EDT.
Following the London game vs the Jets, the Miami Dolphins play the Tennessee Titans on the road in Nashville after their bye week. The Dolphins also have away games left this season vs the Philadelphia Eagles, the San Diego Chargers and their divisional rivals the New England Patriots, Buffalo Bills and the Jets. The Miami Dolphins also have games left after this week at home vs the Houston Texans, the Dallas Cowboys, the Baltimore Ravens, the New York Giants, the Indianapolis Colts as well as vs divisional rival the Patriots.
That is not an easy schedule the Miami Dolphins have in 2015. The game vs the Jets is considered a home game for the Dolphins and they really need to beat the Jets to get back to .500 and get the season going in the right direction. The Dolphins have played in London twice before and the team is 1-1 playing in England.
Hope you enjoy the photos of the craziest Miami Dolphins NFL fans in 2015. Watch for the craziest Dolphins fans from the photos at the rest of the teams NFL games this season including this week in Wembley Stadium in London, England.
